{
    "id": "composting/start",
    "title": "Start a Compost Bucket",
    "description": "Build a compost bucket, learn the science, and run the setup process from item pages.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/compost_start_bucket.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/nova.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Waste not, friend! We'll build your first compost bucket and I'll coach you through where to run the process.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "ux-hint",
                    "text": "I am new. Walk me through it step-by-step."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "I know the basics\u2014quiz me first."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "ux-hint",
            "text": "First, open your Inventory and find the required item pages (5 gallon bucket and work gloves). In DSPACE, processes live on item pages, not inside the quest chat.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "ux-hint-2",
                    "text": "Got it. What should I click once I open those item pages?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "ux-hint-2",
            "text": "On each item page, scroll to the Processes section. Look for the process card title, check required inputs, then verify the output item before pressing Run.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials",
                    "text": "Nice. Teach me compost setup and ratios."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Quiz me before I run anything."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "materials",
            "text": "You need a vented 5 gallon bucket, gloves, and organic matter. We use hydroponic basil trimmings as greens, then cover with dry browns so the mix stays balanced.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "qa",
                    "text": "Why does that green/brown balance matter?"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Let me prove I understand with the quiz."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "qa",
            "text": "Greens add nitrogen and moisture; browns add carbon and airflow. Aim near 1 part greens to 2 parts browns by volume so microbes stay active without odor.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "run-process-hint",
                    "text": "Where exactly do I run the compost process?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1",
            "text": "Quiz 1: Which mix usually composts fastest without getting slimy?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "About 1 part greens to 2 parts browns"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-ratio",
                    "text": "All greens, packed tightly"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-ratio",
                    "text": "Only dry browns forever"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-retry-ratio",
            "text": "Close. Too many greens can turn anaerobic; too many browns stalls decomposition. Try again.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2",
            "text": "Quiz 2: What moisture target should your bucket feel like?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "Like a wrung-out sponge"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-moisture",
                    "text": "Bone dry so mold cannot grow"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-moisture",
                    "text": "Dripping wet at all times"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-retry-moisture",
            "text": "Not quite. Compost microbes need moisture and oxygen. Soggy buckets lose airflow; dry buckets go dormant.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3",
            "text": "Quiz 3: Why do we turn or fluff compost regularly?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "To add oxygen for aerobic microbes"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-air",
                    "text": "To make it look pretty only"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-air",
                    "text": "To remove all moisture"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-retry-air",
            "text": "Nope. Turning is mainly aeration; oxygen keeps decomposition efficient and less smelly.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-4",
            "text": "Quiz 4: Which item should stay out of this bucket?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-5",
                    "text": "Meat and oily leftovers"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-avoid",
                    "text": "Basil trimmings"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-avoid",
                    "text": "Shredded cardboard"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-retry-avoid",
            "text": "Try again. Meat and oils can attract pests and create odor in a beginner bucket system.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-5",
            "text": "Quiz 5: What core temperature range usually signals active hot composting?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-6",
                    "text": "About 55\u201365\u00b0C (131\u2013149\u00b0F)"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-temp",
                    "text": "0\u201310\u00b0C (32\u201350\u00b0F)"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-temp",
                    "text": "95\u2013110\u00b0C (203\u2013230\u00b0F)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-retry-temp",
            "text": "Not that range. Active compost is warm, but not near boiling.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-5",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-6",
            "text": "Quiz 6: You see fruit flies. What is the best first fix?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "run-process-hint",
                    "text": "Bury fresh scraps and add a thicker brown cap"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-pests",
                    "text": "Add more sweet fruit to distract them"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-retry-pests",
                    "text": "Seal the bucket with no vent holes"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-retry-pests",
            "text": "Good instinct to react quickly, but the fix is to hide greens under browns and keep airflow.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-6",
                    "text": "Retry quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "run-process-hint",
            "text": "Now execute the build. Open the 5 gallon bucket item page, go to its Processes section, run \"Vent and layer a kitchen compost bucket,\" and confirm it consumes a bundle of basil leaves and a harvested basil plant and outputs a layered compost bucket.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "start-compost-bin",
                    "goto": "run-process-hint",
                    "text": "Run the compost setup process"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "025862b3-8377-4396-ab32-aa572bdc3260",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ],
                    "text": "I ran it on the item page and made a layered compost bucket."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Excellent setup. Your bucket is active, your process navigation skills are stronger, and you earned gardening supplies for the next grow cycle.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "025862b3-8377-4396-ab32-aa572bdc3260",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ],
                    "text": "Compost bucket started"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "rewards": [
        {
            "id": "cfaa44c1-86b4-43ae-b15e-11e3ad75ba57",
            "count": 2
        },
        {
            "id": "4796b4a9-0927-4b46-a41f-076ebaff01bb",
            "count": 1
        }
    ],
    "requiresQuests": ["hydroponics/basil"],
